3. Implement `mergedTools` / `activePluginNamespaces` — same file

   ```dart
   @override
   Set<String> activePluginNamespaces() {
     return <String>{
       for (final p in _session.handshake.plugins)
         if (_pluginTools.containsKey(p.namespace) &&
             !_disabled.contains(p.namespace)) p.namespace,
     };
   }

   @override
   List<ToolDescriptor> mergedTools() {
     final out = <ToolDescriptor>[..._coreTools];
     for (final ns in activePluginNamespaces()) {
       out.addAll(_pluginTools[ns]!);
     }
     return List.unmodifiable(out);
   }
   ```
   Test: `dart analyze packages/exploration_agent` → 0 issues
   Commit: `feat(exploration_agent): mergedTools/activePluginNamespaces`

4. Implement idempotent `disablePlugin` — same file

