3. Implement `PolicyLoop` — `exploration_flutter/lib/src/observation/policy_loop.dart`

   `PolicyLoop` constructor takes: `FrameworkBusySnapshot Function() snapshot`, `List<RegisteredPlugin> plugins`, `int Function() semHash`, `int Function() routeHash`. Its `Future<Tick> run(ObservationRequest req)` loops until termination, awaiting `SchedulerBinding.instance.endOfFrame` between iterations. Each iteration:

   ```dart
   final fw = snapshot();
   final busy = await _collectBusy(plugins); // try/catch each; throwing => not busy + strike via registry
   final fwIdle = !fw.anyBusy;
   final pIdle  = busy.every((b) => !b.isBusy);
   final ms     = DateTime.now().difference(start).inMilliseconds;
   final pBusy  = [for (final b in busy) if (b.isBusy)
       PluginBusy(b.namespace, reason: b.reason, estMs: b.estimatedDuration?.inMilliseconds)];
   ```

   Per policy:
   - `actionRelative`: terminate `routeChange` if `routeHash() != initRoute`; `semanticsChange` if `semHash() != initSem`; `idle` if `fwIdle && pIdle`; `budget` if `ms >= req.actionRelativeBudgetMs`.
   - `quietFrame`: maintain `quiet` counter; `quiet = (fwIdle && pIdle) ? quiet+1 : 0`; terminate `quietFrame` when `quiet >= req.quietFrameN`.
   - `boundedStability`: same quiet counter rule; terminate `quietFrame` on streak; terminate `budget` if `ms >= req.boundedStabilityBudgetMs`. On `budget` include `pBusy`; on quietFrame/idle return `pluginsBusy: const []`.

