design:
## Approach
HTTP client targeting GPT-5-class via OpenAI Chat Completions tools[] API. Implements `ModelProvider` (.14). `tool_calls[]` (`function.name` + JSON-string `function.arguments`) → `ModelDecision`. Reuses shared frontier helpers (`FrontierDefaults`, `VisionImage`, `validateToolArgs`, `lookupTool`) from .36. Vision via `image_url` parts. Schema-rejection retry-once. Web-compatible HTTP only.

## Constraints
- Web-compatible per PRD §22 — no dart:io. HTTP via `package:http`.
- Frontier-tier defaults reused from .36.
- vision=per-model; preserveThinking has no OpenAI equivalent.
- Schema validation reuses .14's `ActionSchema`.

## Ruled out
- `openai_dart` package: thin HTTP layer keeps capability + schema hooks under our control.
- Sharing parser code with .36: tool_use blocks vs tool_calls don't dedup cleanly.

## Non-obvious notes
- Strictly depends on .36 for shared helpers (per .36's `## Touches`); do NOT duplicate.
- .18 (loop driver) depends on .36 AND .37 — convergence point.
- Streaming variant feeds DevTools thinking panel (.23).
- Pin to modern `tools[]`/`tool_calls[]`, not deprecated `functions[]`.

## Implementation Plan

1. Model registry — `packages/exploration_agent/lib/src/provider/openai/openai_models.dart`

   ```dart
   import '../types.dart';
   class OpenAiModel {
     final String id; final ModelCapabilities capabilities;
     const OpenAiModel({required this.id, required this.capabilities});
   }
   const _vision = ModelCapabilities(vision: true, preserveThinking: false,
     maxContext: 400000, supportsToolUse: true);
   const Map<String, OpenAiModel> openAiModels = {
     'gpt-5':      OpenAiModel(id: 'gpt-5',      capabilities: _vision),
     'gpt-5-mini': OpenAiModel(id: 'gpt-5-mini', capabilities: _vision),
   };
   ```

   **Test:** `dart analyze packages/exploration_agent/lib/src/provider/openai/openai_models.dart` → `No issues found!`
   **Commit:** `feat(exploration_agent): add OpenAI model registry`

2. Request builder — `packages/exploration_agent/lib/src/provider/openai/openai_request.dart`

   Top-level pure fn `buildOpenAiRequest({required String model, required PromptPayload prompt, required ActionSchema schema, required FrontierDefaults defaults, bool stream = false, String? schemaErrorNote}) -> Map<String,dynamic>`. Imports `../types.dart`, `../action_schema.dart`, `../frontier/frontier_defaults.dart`, `../frontier/vision_image.dart`. Body shape:

   - `model`: passthrough
   - `messages`:
     - `[{role:'system', content: prompt.systemMessage}]`
     - if `schemaErrorNote != null`: append `{role:'system', content: 'Previous response failed schema validation: $schemaErrorNote. Reply with a tool_call matching the declared tools.'}`
     - for each `um` in `prompt.userMessages`: append `{role:'user', content: parts}` where `parts` collects `{type:'text', text: um['text']}` (when present) and `{type:'image_url', image_url:{url:'data:${s.mimeType};base64,${s.base64}'}}` (when `um['screenshot']` is `VisionImage s`)
   - `tools`: `prompt.tools.map((t) => {type:'function', function:{name:t.name, description:t.description, parameters:t.inputSchema}}).toList()`
   - `tool_choice`: `'required'`
   - `temperature`/`top_p`/`max_completion_tokens` from `defaults`
   - `stream: true` only if `stream` param true

   **Test:** `dart analyze packages/exploration_agent/lib/src/provider/openai/openai_request.dart` → `No issues found!`
   **Commit:** `feat(exploration_agent): add OpenAI request builder`

3. Response parser — `packages/exploration_agent/lib/src/provider/openai/openai_parse.dart`

   Top-level `parseOpenAiResponse(Map<String,dynamic> body, {required ActionSchema schema, required List<ToolDescriptor> tools}) -> ModelDecision`. Imports `dart:convert`, `../types.dart`, `../action_schema.dart`, `../frontier/tool_validation.dart` (.36).

   Throws `SchemaRejection(validationError, rawOutput: jsonEncode(body))` when:
   - `body['choices']` is null/empty (`'no choices'`)
   - `choices[0].message.tool_calls` is null/empty (`'no tool_calls'`)
   - `tool_calls[0].function.arguments` not valid JSON (`'bad arg JSON: $e'`, `rawOutput` = the raw arguments string)

   On success extracts `name = fn.name`, `args = jsonDecode(fn.arguments)`, then calls `lookupTool(tools, name)` and `validateToolArgs(schema: schema, toolName: name, args: args)` (both .36 helpers; both throw `SchemaRejection` on miss/invalid).

   Optional sibling `message.content` (String): wrap in try/catch, `jsonDecode` and read `summary_update`, `rationale`, `wait_strategy` keys; non-JSON content silently ignored.

   Returns `ModelDecision(action: (tool: tool.name, args: args), summaryUpdate: ..., rationale: ..., waitStrategy: ...)`.

   **Test:** `dart analyze packages/exploration_agent/lib/src/provider/openai/openai_parse.dart` → `No issues found!`
   **Commit:** `feat(exploration_agent): add OpenAI response parser`

4. Provider class — `packages/exploration_agent/lib/src/provider/openai/openai_provider.dart`

   ```dart
   import 'dart:async'; import 'dart:convert';
   import 'package:http/http.dart' as http;
   import '../types.dart'; import '../action_schema.dart';
   import '../model_provider.dart';
   import '../frontier/frontier_defaults.dart';
   import 'openai_models.dart';
   import 'openai_request.dart';
   import 'openai_parse.dart';

   class OpenAiModelProvider implements ModelProvider {
     final String modelId, apiKey;
     final Uri endpoint;
     final http.Client _client;
     final FrontierDefaults _defaults;
     final _thinking = StreamController<ThinkingDelta>.broadcast();

     OpenAiModelProvider({required this.modelId, required this.apiKey,
       Uri? endpoint, http.Client? client, FrontierDefaults? defaults})
       : endpoint = endpoint ?? Uri.parse('https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions'),
         _client = client ?? http.Client(),
         _defaults = defaults ?? FrontierDefaults.openai();

     @override
     ModelCapabilities get capabilities {
       final m = openAiModels[modelId];
       if (m == null) throw ArgumentError('unknown model: $modelId');
       return m.capabilities;
     }
     @override
     Stream<ThinkingDelta> thinking() => _thinking.stream;

     @override
     Future<ModelDecision> decide(PromptPayload p, ActionSchema s) async {
       try { return await _attempt(p, s, null); }
       on SchemaRejection catch (e) { return await _attempt(p, s, e.validationError); }
     }

     Future<ModelDecision> _attempt(PromptPayload p, ActionSchema s, String? note) async {
       final body = buildOpenAiRequest(model: modelId, prompt: p, schema: s,
         defaults: _defaults, schemaErrorNote: note);
       final res = await _client.post(endpoint, headers: {
         'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'Authorization': 'Bearer $apiKey',
       }, body: jsonEncode(body));
       if (res.statusCode >= 400) {
         throw StateError('openai http ${res.statusCode}: ${res.body}');
       }
       return parseOpenAiResponse(jsonDecode(res.body) as Map<String, dynamic>,
         schema: s, tools: p.tools);
     }

     Future<void> streamThinking(PromptPayload prompt, ActionSchema schema) async {
       final body = buildOpenAiRequest(model: modelId, prompt: prompt,
         schema: schema, defaults: _defaults, stream: true);
       final req = http.Request('POST', endpoint)
         ..headers['Content-Type'] = 'application/json'
         ..headers['Authorization'] = 'Bearer $apiKey'
         ..body = jsonEncode(body);
       final res = await _client.send(req);
       await for (final line in res.stream
           .transform(utf8.decoder).transform(const LineSplitter())) {
         if (!line.startsWith('data: ')) continue;
         final p = line.substring(6).trim();
         if (p == '[DONE]') {
           _thinking.add(const ThinkingDelta(text: '', isFinal: true));
           return;
         }
         final m = jsonDecode(p) as Map<String, dynamic>;
         final d = ((m['choices'] as List).first as Map)['delta'] as Map?;
         final t = d?['content'] as String?;
         if (t != null && t.isNotEmpty) {
           _thinking.add(ThinkingDelta(text: t, isFinal: false));
         }
       }
     }

     Future<void> close() async { await _thinking.close(); _client.close(); }
   }
   ```

