## Approach
Virtualized scrollable list of `TrajectoryRecord` rows backed by a `ValueNotifier<List<TrajectoryRecord>>` that grows live (subscribes to .19's writer broadcast) or is hydrated from JSONL (parsed by a new `TrajectoryReader` shipped beside the writer in `exploration_agent`; file bytes via DTD APIs from .21). Three-line row: action / diff / running summary. Tap pushes detail view with full observation, plugin fragments, reasoning, action, validation, screenshot — all lazily rendered. `ListView.builder` keyed on turn index for virtualization; `ValueListenableBuilder` over append-only notifier avoids rebuilding existing rows. Mode toggle swaps `LiveTimelineSource` <-> `BrowseTimelineSource`.

## Constraints
- JSONL schema must match .19's writer exactly.
- No `dart:io` in package code (PRD §22).
- Detail view lazy-renders screenshots and full semantics tree.
- 6000-turn / ~50MB trajectory must scroll at <16ms/frame.

## Ruled out
- Separate live/post-session render paths.
- Inline observation in row (detail-on-tap).
- Trajectory analytics, search, multi-session compare (out of v1).

