## Approach
Thin Dart console app under cli/ (.1) using `package:args`. Composes `ExplorationSession` (.11) + `LoopDriver` (.18): parse flags, build provider via per-tier defaults (.14/.15/.16), open `FileTrajectorySink` (this bead) wrapping `TrajectoryWriter` (.19), attach stdout progress listener, run driver. AGENTS.md at `packages/exploration_cli/templates/AGENTS.md`; `--help` prints that path. Per-tier defaults per PRD §16.4: qwen-mlx → MLX defaults, claude → Sonnet, openai → GPT-5.

## Constraints
- CLI is `dart:io`-bound (intentional; complements DevTools .21).
- No loop logic in CLI — comes from `LoopDriver`/`ExplorationSession`.
- `--goal` flag wins over stdin; stdin used when omitted and not a TTY.
- Default output: `./trajectories/<UTC-timestamp>.jsonl`.
- Exit codes: 0 clean, 64 usage, 1 harness error per §17.

## Ruled out
- Reimplementing loop in CLI — both frontends share .18 per §6.2.
- Auto-launching `flutter run` — out of scope.
- Rich TUI — plain stdout suffices for v1.
- Bundling AGENTS.md content into `--help` text — path reference suffices.

